The paper focuses on storing and querying large-scale spatio-temporal graphs, which involves data management and processing. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the design goals of the framework, which involves data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely category as well. The paper also mentions the challenges of processing spatio-temporal graphs, which involves distributed computing and parallel processing, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a likely category. The paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed framework, which involves performance evaluation and optimization, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) likely categories as well.
